{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Aeneas tackles the imbalanced data problem by generating synthesized failing test cases using a conditional variational autoencoder (CVAE) from the reduced feature space.Hu et al. [528] proposed Lamont, which uses revised linear discriminant analysis to reduce the dimensionality of the original coverage matrix and leverages synthetic minority over-sampling (SMOTE) to generate the synthesized failing tests.Lei et al.",
    "[529] proposed BCL-FL, a data augmentation approach based on between-class learning.",
    "By leveraging the characteristics of real failed test cases, BCL-FL produces synthesized samples that closely resemble real test cases.",
    "The mixing ratio of original labels is used to assign a continuous value between 0 and 1 to the synthesized samples.",
    "This ensures a balanced input dataset for FL techniques."
  ],
